\f1\fs32 Mass is a fundamental property of matter that quantifies the amount of substance within an object. It is a measure of an object's resistance to acceleration when a force is applied, and it also determines the strength of its gravitational attraction to other objects.  The greater the mass of an object, the heavier it is on earth and the more force is required to accelerate or decelerate it. \
