\cf0 Force is any action that tends to maintain, alter or distort the motion of a body.  Force can be caused by contact with another object, or due to the remote effects of gravity, magnetism, or other influences.  More simply, a force is a push or a pull.  One common example of force is weight, which is the effect of gravity on a mass.
